beer.beer_description:
Myall Marzen is a German style malty lager.  It is rich in malt with a balance of clean, hop bitterness. This style was traditionally brewed in Germany in the spring (Marzen means March) and aged/lagered through the summer ready for Octoberfest.

Myall Marzen was designed by Scott Jardine and was the winner of the 2020 The Coastal Brewing Company / FnT Brew Supplies home brew competition and is named after the Myall Lakes National Park in the Barrington Coast area of NSW.
